      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All samples from production lots with full traceability. Sample dimensions and material certs confirmed consistent with FEA model inputs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU loading scenarios; at minimum two distinct load levels or configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single compression-bending load configuration per ASTM F1717 standard protocol. While this is the regulatory standard condition, only one test condition was evaluated, limiting the ability to assess model behavior across the full COU loading envelope. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given regulatory standard alignment."
