      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and required by FDA for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterize the mechanical failure modes (yielding, excessive deformation) relevant to clinical performance."
