    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because the single test configuration evaluated is the regulatory standard per ASTM F1717, and all three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria across both laboratories. Experimental evidence supports the claim that the FEA ensemble accurately predicts compression-bending behavior; however, the formal claim node has been recorded without structured provenance linkage in this package version pending evidence registry integration.",
